{"ts":"2026-07-19T16:09:04.938Z","author":"codex-wide-sdk-20260719","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/comments/1","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-19T16:09:04.938Z","author":"codex-wide-sdk-20260719","text":"Final implementation correction: PmCreateActionOptions, PmUpdateActionOptions, and PmCloseActionOptions now derive from the executable CLI command option interfaces after stripping index signatures and internal runtime/policy keys, rather than deriving client options from MCP tool aliases. PmClient methods and the top-level create/update/close SDK helpers all consume these strict types. Compile-time tests reject typos, wrong scalar kinds such as priority=true, MCP-only aliases such as estimate, object/array values, and unsupported keys while accepting real client keys such as estimatedMinutes and file. pnpm typecheck and the full coverage suite pass."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T16:09:04.938Z"}],"before_hash":"ac64607ac578cbea859534fe8e211d58fe2cb40084642064082043782d56f2bc","after_hash":"52b20dcec993f1d6f3e73bd516320cd83a9d2d1cd68a092346773f9a983551cc"}
{"ts":"2026-07-19T16:09:05.804Z","author":"codex-wide-sdk-20260719","op":"learning_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/learnings/1","value":{"created_at":"2026-07-19T16:09:05.803Z","author":"codex-wide-sdk-20260719","text":"Public SDK client option types must derive from the executable command option interfaces, not transport-specific MCP aliases; otherwise accepted keys drift from runtime behavior even when a schema-derived type looks strict. Strip index signatures before projecting public mutation inputs so excess-property checks remain effective."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-19T16:09:05.804Z"}],"before_hash":"52b20dcec993f1d6f3e73bd516320cd83a9d2d1cd68a092346773f9a983551cc","after_hash":"eb90ed1c4f1fe36bc8e05ecdb1a3b3e149cb555b00bff08c368579702fdfc3eb"}
